The '''nashtah''', also known as a '''Dravian hound''', was a six-[[Limb/Legends|legged]] predatory [[Reptile/Legends|reptile]] from the [[Mountain/Legends|mountains]] of [[Dra III]].

These intelligent, bloodthirsty pack hunters were the only animals from that [[Planet/Legends|world]] to ever be domesticated. Their claws and [[Tooth/Legends|teeth]] were diamond-hard, allowing them to dig prey out of formations of basaltic rock. Their barbed tails and saliva contained a venom that marked their prey, allowing them to unswervingly track it for up to a month after contact. Their [[Color/Legends|coloration]] ranged from dark brown to green.

[[File:Nashtah_TotG.jpg|thumb|left|250px|A group of nashtahs hunting an [[Eopie/Legends|eopie]].]]
In the wild, nashtahs often outsmarted or outlasted animals with greater size, speed, or viciousness. The first survey teams to the world were wiped out by Dra III's native life, but eventually a team escaped the world alive with several dead nashtahs, and subsequently the creatures became the most studied lifeform from the world. Some prominent criminals used Dravian hounds as guard animals despite the fact they are as likely to attack their masters as protect them.

The [[Slavery/Legends|slavers]] [[Magg]] and [[Zlarb/Legends|Zlarb]] used nashtahs in their slaving operations, including one on [[Lur]]. The [[Tunroth]], [[Shotarr Kass]], had a pet nashtah that he called "[[Klirun (nashtah)|Klirun]]."<ref name="SotSR">''[[Secrets of the Sisar Run]]''</ref> [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] had a nashtah-skin throne onboard her ship the [[Last Chance (YT-1300 light freighter)/Legends|''Last Chance'']].<ref name="IDC">''[[Imperial Double-Cross]]''</ref>

During her time as a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], [[Aurra Sing/Legends|Aurra Sing]] received the nickname "Nashtah" from the [[The Dark Woman|Dark Woman]].<ref name="Jedi: Aayla Secura">''[[Jedi: Aayla Secura]]''</ref>

One nashtah injured scout [[Barosa Warren]]'s right arm, causing him a permanent scar, while he was scouting Dra III for the Old Republic.<ref name="air">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref>

[[Suroc]] purchased a nashtah on [[Andasala]].<ref name="GG11">''[[Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations]]''</ref>

